ol.steps
  if this.pluginURL
    li
      != this.renderDownloadLink()
      p After downloading, don’t unzip the file.

    li
      h2 Login to your Drupal Administrator Dashboard and click <strong>Extend</strong>.

      figure(data-ref="screenshotMounts[]" data-screenshot="navigateToModules")

    li
      h2 Click <strong>Install new module</strong>.

      figure(data-ref="screenshotMounts[]" data-screenshot="installNewModules")

    li
      h2 Upload the module.
      p Click <strong>Choose File</strong> and select the module you downloaded to your computer.

      figure(data-ref="screenshotMounts[]" data-screenshot="uploadModule")

    li
      h2 Activate the module.

      p You should see the new module on the <strong>Extend</strong> page.
      p The module will appear in category set by the author.
      p Click the checkbox next to the module, then click <strong>Save Configuration</strong>.

      figure(data-ref="screenshotMounts[]" data-screenshot="activateModule")

      p You’re done!

  else
    li
      h2 In your Drupal site’s Admin interface, click the <strong>Structure <span class="with-more-icon-after"></span> Block layout <span class="with-more-icon-after"></span> Add custom block</strong> link in the navigation menu at the top of the page.

    li
      h2 Fill out the form.

      p As the <strong>Block Description</strong> enter “#{ config.name } Embed”.

      p <strong>Before pasting the embed code</strong> as the <strong>Text Format</strong> select “Full HTML”.

      p In the <strong>Body</strong> field click the <strong>Source</strong> button inside the editor.
      p Paste this embed code:

      .copy-container
        button.primary.run(data-ref="copyButtons[]") Copy
        div.copyable(contenteditable)= this.copyText

      p Click <strong>Save</strong>.

      p On the new page that opens, For the <strong>Region</strong> select “Footer first”.

    li
      h2 Click <strong>Save block</strong>, you’re done!
